cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

The paper deals with using mobile phones to track the spread of diseases through proximity interactions among people. This falls under the category of social networks and computational social science (cs.SOC), as well as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) since it involves collecting and analyzing sensitive personal data. The paper also uses machine learning techniques to model the spread of diseases based on partial observations, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Overall, cs.SI (social and information networks) is the most likely category, followed by cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.CYBER, and cs.IR.
